contentrichtext.text: {{wiktionary|placebo effect}} '''Placebo effect''' may refer to: * [[Placebo]] effect, the tendency of any medication or treatment, even an inert or ineffective one, to exhibit results simply because the recipient believes that it will work * [[Placebo Effect (Doctor Who)|''Placebo Effect'' (Doctor Who)]], an original novel written by Gary Russell and based on the long-running British science fiction television series ''Doctor Who'' * "[[The Placebo Effect]]", an episode of the science fiction television series 2002 revival of ''The Twilight Zone'' * [[Placebo Effect (band)]], German dark electro band {{disambiguation}}
